CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 22, 1951, pg. 9, reads: "Courier Trophy Winners - Earl Johnson, center, Courier columnist, is shown presenting to Evan Smalley, manager of the Pittsburgh Stars, a trophy for first place honors in the Courier baseball tournament recently completed.  That's Harold Tinker, manager of the Terrace Village team which finished second, looking on."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Courier columnist Earl Johnson presenting Courier baseball tournament trophies to baseball team managers Evan Smalley and Harold Tinker, Harris Studio
